An open-source, file based MIDI sequencer written in Processing.

THIS IS A WORK IN PROGRESS!

In write mode, it takes input from the keyboard and writes text files that represent MIDI sequences.
In read mode, it reads text files and sends their contents as MIDI messages.

REFERENCES:
Processing -- http://processing.org
MIDIBus library: http://smallbutdigital.com/themidibus.php|
LoopBe internal MIDI port: http://nerds.de/en/loopbe1.html |
OSX alternative to LoopBe -- ipMIDI (Not Yet Tested!): http://nerds.de/en/ipmidi_osx.html


